Data

Data packages

The sample datasets, because of their size, are provided in separate data packages.

  • midfieldstudent: student and degree data
  • midfieldcourse: course data
  • midfieldterm: term data

Smaller data sets bundled with the midfieldr package include cip for the CIP academic program codes and several preformatted datasets used to illustrate specific case studies.

To install the data packages:

# data packages
install_github("graphdr/midfieldstudent")
install_github("graphdr/midfieldterm")
install_github("graphdr/midfieldcourse")

Student data

The midfieldstudent package provides student, a data frame with 165 072 observations, each a unique student, and 35 demographic variables.

The dataset format and variable definitions are described on the help page:

library(midfieldstudent)
?student

To examine the data:

# the amount of memory occupied by the data 
library(pryr)
object_size(student)
#> 49.1 MB

# dimensions, variables, and first few data entries  
library(tibble)
glimpse(student)

CIP code data

The midfieldr package includes cip, a data frame with 2002 observations, each an academic program, and 2 variables.

The dataset format and variable definitions are described on the help page:

library(midfieldr)
?cip

To examine the data:

# the amount of memory occupied by the data 
object_size(cip)
#> 288 kB

# dimensions, variables, and first few data entries  
glimpse(cip)
#> Observations: 2,002
#> Variables: 2
#> $ code <chr> "01", "03", "04", "05", "09", "10", "11", "12", "13", "14...
#> $ name <chr> "Agriculture/Agricultural Operations and Related Sciences...
